(US Employee Policy Handbook) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
() Tj
T*
/F2 12 Tf
(1. Working Hours) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(Standard working hours are Monday through Friday, 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM.) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(Employees may request flexible scheduling with manager approval.) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(Overtime must be authorized in advance and is compensated at 1.5x the) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(regular hourly rate for non-exempt employees.) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
() Tj
T*
/F2 12 Tf
(2. Paid Time Off) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(Full-time employees accrue 15 days of paid vacation per year, increasing) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(to 20 days after five years of service. Unused vacation may carry over up) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(to a maximum of 5 days into the following calendar year.) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(Employees also receive 10 paid sick days and 11 company holidays annually.) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
() Tj
T*
/F2 12 Tf
(3. Remote Work) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(Employees may work remotely up to three days per week. Remote employees) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(must be reachable during core hours \(10:00 AM to 3:00 PM local time\) and) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(maintain a secure internet connection that complies with the IT security) Tj
T*
/F1 10 Tf
(policy described in Section 5.) Tj
T*
ET
